# Atomic Commits

- Only commit when the user explicitly asks.
- Keep commits focused on one workflow/module/tooling concern.
- Do not include secrets, generated run outputs, caches, or machine-local samplesheets.
- Before any requested commit, inspect status, diff, and recent log; stage only relevant files.
- Use messages that describe the workflow or lifecycle surface changed.
